18/05/2003
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- SFOR said on Saturday (17 May) the armed forces of the BiH federation had agreed on the outline of a joint military doctrine. 
The Working Group for a Joint Military Doctrine met on Thursday, hammering out the text using previously adopted documents. 
The doctrine stipulates joint efforts for protection of sovereignty and territorial integrity, support for peace operations and military aid to civilian authorities. 
SFOR described the move as an important step on the road to Partnership for Peace membership. 
(SRNA - 17/05/03)
